itemDescription: British sculptor and jewellery designer (1882–1955 or 1960)

wikipedia_page.main: Margaret Ethel Pye (1882–1960) was a British sculptor who worked in bronze and wood. In the 1910s she also created jewellery, of which some examples still remain. She was a member of a group of literary and artistic friends nicknamed by Virginia Woolf the "neo-pagans".
